#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/gtk/GtkVTKRenderWindowInteractor.py:9
msgid ""
"Provides a pyGtk vtkRenderWindowInteractor widget.  This embeds a   "
"vtkRenderWindow inside a GTK widget and uses the   "
"vtkGenericRenderWindowInteractor for the event handling.  This is   based on "
"vtkTkRenderWindow.py."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/gtk/GtkVTKRenderWindowInteractor.py:14
msgid ""
"The class uses the gtkgl.GtkGLArea widget (gtkglarea).  This avoids   a lot "
"of problems with flicker."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/gtk/GtkVTKRenderWindowInteractor.py:17
msgid "There is a working example at the bottom."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/gtk/GtkVTKRenderWindowInteractor.py:19
msgid "Created by Prabhu Ramachandran, April 2002."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/gtk/GtkVTKRenderWindowInteractor.py:21
msgid "Bugs:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/gtk/GtkVTKRenderWindowInteractor.py:23
msgid ""
"(*) There is a focus related problem.  Tkinter has a focus object   that "
"handles focus events.  I don't know of an equivalent object   under GTK.  "
"So, when an 'enter_notify_event' is received on the   GtkVTKRenderWindow I "
"grab the focus but I don't know what to do when   I get a "
"'leave_notify_event'."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/gtk/GtkVTKRenderWindowInteractor.py:29
msgid ""
"(*) Will not work under Win32 because it uses the XID of a window in   "
"OnRealize.  Suggestions to fix this will be appreciated."
msgstr ""

